Sample questionsfor Mid-quizPart 1: True or False Questions1. The k-Nearest Neighbor (KNN) algorithm performs better when increasing the number of nearest neighbors K.2. When applying the stochastic gradient descent algorithm to optimize a neural network, the loss may increase after a weight update.
Part 2: Multiple-choice Questions (only one correct choice)3. (1 correct choice only) Which of the following is true about the momentum update rule?A. It has no hyperparameters.B. It guarantees convergence to the global optimum.C. If the network has n parameters, momentum requires that we keep track of O(n) extraparameters.D. None of the above.4. (1 correct choice only) If your input image is 32 (width) × 32 (height) × 16 (channels), how many learnable parameters are there in a 1 (width) x1 (height) convolution filter including the bias?A. 2. B. 16. C. 17. D. 32.Sol: 1 False; 2 True ;3 C; 4 C;
